@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About URL Shortener";
}

<div class="container">
    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <div class="about-content">
        <h2>How Our URL Shortener Works</h2>
        
        <p>Our URL shortener service uses a Base62 encoding algorithm to generate short, unique URLs. Here's how it works:</p>
        
        <h3>1. Base62 Encoding</h3>
        <p>We use Base62 encoding (using characters A-Z, a-z, and 0-9) because:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>It's URL-safe (no special characters)</li>
            <li>It's case-sensitive, allowing for more combinations</li>
            <li>It's human-readable and easy to share</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2. Collision Detection</h3>
        <p>To ensure uniqueness, our system:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Checks if the generated short code already exists</li>
            <li>If a collision is detected, generates a new code</li>
            <li>Uses a counter to ensure unique codes even with identical input URLs</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3. Performance Optimization</h3>
        <p>For optimal performance, we:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Cache frequently accessed URLs</li>
            <li>Use efficient database indexing</li>
            <li>Implement rate limiting to prevent abuse</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>
